The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, March 23: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) today deferred the implementation of Clause 49 of the listing agreement till December 31 as many firms are not prepared to comply with it, said chairman M. Damodaran. According to the clause, in case the chairman of a listed firm is an executive director, half of its board members should be independent directors. If the chairman is a non-executive director, then one-third of the board should be independent directors.

 Mumbai, March 23: Jindal Vijaynagar Steel re-listed on the bourses today after its merger with Jindal Iron amp; Steel Company. The merged JVSL opened at Rs 444 on BSE and closed lower at Rs 388.80.

 Mumbai, March 23: Tata Teleservices Maharashtra today approved the allotment of 2.60 crore shares of Rs 10 each to investors who have exercised their right to convert foreign currency convertible bonds held by them into equity.

 Mumbai, March 23: The Centre is planning to raise the 10 per cent allotment limit for domestic investors, including retail investors, in the proposed divestment of public sector units.

 Bangalore, March 23: Maruti today said the diesel engine plant at Manesar in Haryana will be operational by the first quarter of 2007. 




